                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-148" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE CHIDGZEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I took the prisoner into custody on the 23rd of July, at Holborn-bridge—I understood he had acknowledged taking the spoon and asked him where he had pawned it—he said in London-wall—I went there with the prosecutor and he identified it.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner put in a written defence pleading poverty.)</p>
